# .gitignore: threat model: LEAK PREVENTION, not bloat prevention
#
# This brain is shared context. The risk is not large files or build artifacts.
# The risk is personal content, secrets, or interaction preferences leaking
# into a shared or public repo. Every pattern here addresses that threat.
#
# Rule: if content is personal (how Claude talks to YOU) or secret
# (credentials, tokens), it must never reach this repo.

# ─── Personal local memory ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Files with .local.md suffix are by convention personal/local variants
# of brain files, never synced.
*.local.md

# The personal/ tier is off-limits to a TEAM brain (the default). In SOLO mode
# (brain.config.json "mode": "solo") a single owner may sync their personal
# layer across their own devices: comment the personal/* line out to enable
# that. The pre-commit guard still confines personal content to personal/ and
# still scans it for secrets in both modes. Re-add the ignore if the brain
# ever converts to team use. personal/INDEX.md (the tier's doc) always ships.
personal/*
!personal/INDEX.md

# ─── Secrets and credentials ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.*
*.secret
secrets/
credentials/
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx

# ─── OS and editor noise ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini

.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ─── Runtime / temp ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
*.tmp
.cache/

# ─── Internal build/QA artifacts (never ship in a shared/public brain) ───────
# Session logs (/log writes here) and dry-run findings name local machines and
# build process. Keep them local; they are not user-facing brain content.
data/session-log.md
meta/*-findings.md
